cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use QIL in academic work, please cite both the software and the accompanying manuscript."
title: "QIL — Quaternionic Invariant Laboratory"
abstract: >-
  An open-source, exact-arithmetic research framework in Rust for studying
  local, low-degree non-commutative invariants over the rational Hamiltonian
  quaternions. QIL machine-checks the boundary theorems of the accompanying
  manuscript: intrinsic bipartite gauge collapse and extrinsic terminal
  abelianization on exactly labelled 3-SAT instances.
type: software
authors:
